<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
Gate 2 — SSAP pre-HNO failure is authoritative; RCL is not consulted.

When the SSAP progressive filter fails at an element above HNO in the hierarchy
(country, A1-A5, or any street name element), the result is immediately authoritative
and the algorithm does NOT fall through to the RCL layer. This is the critical
distinction from an HNO-level SSAP failure (which does fall through to RCL).

This request submits A2=Morton County for Capitol Way, which exists in the provisioned
GIS data only under Burleigh County. SSAP fails at ca:A2 (pre-HNO). The RCL layer
also has Capitol Way provisioned under Burleigh County and would produce a match if
tried, but it must NOT be tried. The expected outcome is a non-conforming result with
ca:A2 as <invalid> and all remaining submitted elements in <unchecked>.
-->
<findService xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:lost1" validateLocation="true">
  <location id="L1" profile="civic">
    <civicAddress xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:pidf:geopriv10:civicAddr">
      <country>US</country>
      <A1>ND</A1>
      <A2>Morton County</A2>
      <A3>Bismarck</A3>
      <RD>Capitol</RD>
      <STS>Way</STS>
      <HNO>1661</HNO>
    </civicAddress>
  </location>
  <service>urn:service:sos</service>
</findService>
